  "rationale": "Howard's craft principle (and modern style guides \u2014 King, Leonard, Strunk) argue for a high said-ratio: 'said' is invisible, alternative tags ('declared', 'spat', 'hissed') call attention to themselves and are usually doing work better done by the surrounding action or dialogue. Measuring Salvatore's actual said-ratio sets the imitator-target for the writer layer and the lint layer's 'replace creative tag with said+action' rule.",
